04/05/2003
STRASBOURG, France -- At the initiative of European Commission President Romano Prodi, the Council of Europe and the EU have drafted a programme for the preservation and rehabilitation of the cultural, archeological and historical heritage in Southeast Europe, Tanjug reported Saturday (3 May).
Under the programme, called the Integrated Rehabilitation Project Plan, European institutions, working with relevant domestic authorities, would conduct a joint survey of important monuments and sites in the region in urgent need of conservation or restoration.
The project would be implemented between 2003 and 2005.
(Tanjug - 03/05/03)
